observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive directs:
a. The Municipal Engineer to provide report on the cost and status of on-going projects and submit details cost of components of infrastructure projects as the need arises for proper recoding in the books of the on-going projects and facilitate the transfer of these projects from the CIP accounts to the appropriate PPE accounts and Registry of Public Infrastructures upon completion;
b. The Municipal Accountant to identify the details of the CIP projects with no details in the ledger card and record the following adjusting entries to transfer the specified CIP to the relevant asset account and correct the errors in recording CIP;
c. The Municipal Accountant, using the adjusted data provided, compute the required depreciation on the completed projects.

Based on the foregoing, we respectfully recommended that management:  

Submit the contract of service of the consultant specifying the duties/functions for review;

Consider the desired expertise, which is not available among the regular staff, in hiring consultants;

Require the submission of DTR’s and accomplishment reports as basis for payment. 

Utilize the services of the permanent employees in discharging regular/ordinary services to compensate and maximize  the costs of their employment; and

Revisit its organizational structure, staffing pattern and service requirements to assess the necessity of hiring a consultant.
